<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3893.1.2>
    dc:creator "Brunke, Adam; Solodovnikov, Alexey" ;
    dc:date "2014" ;
    dc:title "Male secondary sexual characters resolve taxonomic uncertainty: five new species and a review of the formerly monotypic rove beetle genus Mimosticus Sharp (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Staphylininae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.250404>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.250406>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.250408>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.250405>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.250409>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.250410>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.250411>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.250407>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.250412>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.250403> .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.250404>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Antennomeres 4 – 11: Mimosticus viridipennis, Sharp (A), M. tenuiformis Brunke and Solodovnikov (B), M. aeneipennis Brunke and Solodovnikov (C) and M. sharpi Brunke and Solodovnikov (D). Ventral forebody of M. tenuiformis (E). Mesotrochanter and mesofemur of M. tenuiformis (F). Hindwing of M. aeneipennis, vein MP 4 fused to CuA (G). Scale bars = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/250404/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.250406>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Male sternite VIII of Mimosticus viridipennis, Sharp (A), M. tenuiformis Brunke and Solodovnikov (B), M. aeneipennis Brunke and Solodovnikov (C), M. sharpi Brunke and Solodovnikov (D), M. pseudosharpi Brunke and Solodovnikov (E) and M. latens Brunke and Solodovnikov (F). Scale bars = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/250406/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.250408>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Male sternite IX of Mimosticus viridipennis, Sharp (A), M. tenuiformis Brunke and Solodovnikov (B), M. aeneipennis Brunke and Solodovnikov (C), M. sharpi Brunke and Solodovnikov (D), M. pseudosharpi Brunke and Solodovnikov (E) and M. latens Brunke and Solodovnikov (F). Scale bars = 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/250408/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.250405>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Forebody of Mimosticus viridipennis, Sharp (A), M. tenuiformis Brunke and Solodovnikov (B), M. aeneipennis Brunke and Solodovnikov (C) and M. sharpi Brunke and Solodovnikov (D). Scale bars = 1 mm. a—anterior frontal puncture, b—oculomarginal puncture, c—posterior frontal puncture, d—vertical puncture." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/250405/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.250409>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Male tergite X of Mimosticus viridipennis, Sharp (A), M. tenuiformis Brunke and Solodovnikov (B), M. aeneipennis Brunke and Solodovnikov (C), M. sharpi Brunke and Solodovnikov (D), M. pseudosharpi Brunke and Solodovnikov (E) and M. latens Brunke and Solodovnikov (F). Scale bars = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/250409/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.250410>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Aedeagus of Mimosticus viridipennis Sharp (A – D), M. tenuiformis Brunke and Solodovnikov (E) and M. sharpi Brunke and Solodovnikov (F). Parameral view (A – B, E – F), lateral view (C – D). Internal sac not everted (A, C, E, F), internal sac everted (B, D). Scale bars = 0.5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/250410/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.250411>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Abparameral view of median lobe of the aedeagus, showing internal sac in situ: Mimosticus viridipennis, Sharp (A), M. tenuiformis Brunke and Solodovnikov (B), M. aeneipennis Brunke and Solodovnikov (C), M. sharpi Brunke and Solodovnikov (D). Copulatory sclerite of internal sac of M. sharpi (E), M. pseudosharpi Brunke and Solodovnikov (F) and M. latens Brunke and Solodovnikov (G). Scale bars = 0.2 mm. a—ventral apex of paramere showing peg setae-like structures, b—copulatory sclerite, arrow—apical margin of copulatory sclerite." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/250411/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.250407>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Male tergite VIII of M. latens Brunke and Solodovnikov (A). Female tergite X of M. sharpi Brunke and Solodovnikov (B). Scale bars = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/250407/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.250412>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Distribution of Mimosticus aeneipennis Brunke and Solodovnikov, M. latens Brunke and Solodovnikov, M pseudosharpi Brunke and Solodovnikov, and M. viridipennis Sharp (A); and M. tenuiformis Brunke and Solodovnikov, and M. sharpi (B)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/250412/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.250403>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Dorsal habitus of Mimosticus viridipennis, Sharp (A), M. tenuiformis Brunke and Solodovnikov (B), M. aeneipennis Brunke and Solodovnikov (C) and M. sharpi Brunke and Solodovnikov (D). Scale bars = 2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/250403/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

